meanings.english_definition: A muscle which covers parts of the skull. Some sources consider it part of the occipitofrontalis muscle.

examples.sentence: The occipitalis muscle is located at the back of the head.
examples.translation: 後頭筋は頭の後ろに位置しています。

etymology.value: From Latin occipitalis, pertaining to the occiput (back of the head).
